North America
---
USA (Florida) mosquitoes. 1 Sep 2016. (conf.) Zika virus found in 3 pools of mosquitoes trapped in Miami Beach, the 1st time this has happened in the continental U.S. Authorities are blaming water-collecting bromeliad plants for making mosquito control much more difficult.
http://bigstory.ap.org/article/2c5ad7ebf90a4daaac368fd3a06867f1/florida-finds-zika-trapped-mosquitoes-1st-us-mainland

Central America
---
Honduras. 21 Aug 2016. (Conf.) 1 case of Zika virus infection associated sensory polyneuropathy.
http://www.jns-journal.com/article/S0022-510X(16)30535-4/abstract

Nicaragua. 26 Aug 2016. (conf.) 1603 cases of which 799 pregnant; Microcephaly: 1 case Zika virus associated; Locality most affected: Managua 1028 cases.
http://www.el19digital.com/articulos/ver/titulo:45720-nicaragua-confirma-primer-caso-de-microcefalia-por-zika [in Spanish]

Caribbean
---
Cayman Islands. 30 Aug 2016. (conf.) cases increased to 5.
https://www.caymancompass.com/2016/08/30/two-more-zika-cases-confirmed-in-george-town/

Cuba. 2 Sep 2016. (reported) 3 locally acquired cases but a militarized nationwide campaign of intensive mosquito spraying, monitoring and quarantine appears to be working to prevent ongoing transmission.
http://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/cuba-reports-remarkable-success-zika-virus-41815050

Dominican Republic. 1 Sep 2016. (reported) as of week 32, 5109 cases.
http://www.cdn.com.do/noticias/nacional/2016/09/01/salud-registra-30-muertos-por-dengue-en-lo-que-va-de-ano/

[A 2 Sep 2016 report indicated that 920 pregnant women have had Zika virus infections within the 1st 24 weeks of gestation and 3 confirmed cases of microcephaly (http://hoy.com.do/pais-registra-924-embarazadas-tuvieron-zika-virus-va-en-baja/ in Spanish)]

Haiti. 25 Aug 2016. (reported) more than 2000 cases; Declining.
http://www.metropolehaiti.com/metropole/full_une_fr.php?id=29052 [in French]

Puerto Rico:
- Total cases. 26 Aug 2016. (conf.) 14 334 cases; 129 Zika virus infected women have delivered normal babies.
https://vidayestilo.terra.com.co/salud/sin-control-los-contagios-de-zika-entre-embarazadas-de-puerto-rico,bec20d09148bec65e0c7129d4e28a6b35fk5sg3n.html [in Spanish]

- Guillain-Barré syndrome. 2 Sep 2016. (reported) Overall, the 34 persons with suspected Guillain-Barré syndrome (GBS) and evidence of Zika virus or flavivirus infection was 2.5 times greater than the number of persons with suspected GBS and no evidence of Zika virus infection, with an increasing number of cases occurring each month beginning in April 2016.
http://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/volumes/65/wr/mm6534e1.htm?s_cid=mm6534e1_e

South America
---
Zika associated GBS. 1 Sep 2016. (reported) Guillain-Barré syndrome (GBS) rates increase over pre-Zika baseline: Brazil's Bahia State (172 percent increase), Colombia (211 percent), the Dominican Republic (150 percent), El Salvador (100 percent), Honduras (144 percent), Suriname (400 percent), and Venezuela (877 percent).
http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/zika-virus-outbreak/study-finds-strong-link-between-zika-paralyzing-guillain-barr-syndrome-n641276

Brazil. 30 Aug 2016. (conf.) 1st case of encephalitis from Zika virus infection in an adult, a 47-year-old female who died. The diagnosis of encephalitis was determined by the presence of a disturbed level of consciousness and focal neurological signs during an exanthemous viral infection. In endemic areas, ZIKV should be considered as an etiological agent in cases of encephalitis, and clinicians should be aware of its potential severity.
http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1386653216305133

Paraguay. 27 Aug 2016. (susp.) 27 Zika virus infection-related cases of microcephaly.
http://prensa-latina.cu/index.php?o=rn&id=22409&SEO=estudian-en-paraguay-27-casos-sospechosos-de-microcefalia-por-zika [in Spanish]

Asia
---
Philippines (lloilo City, Western Visayas region). 5 Sep 2016. (conf.) 1st case in country this year (2016); 45-year-old woman not pregnant; Previous cases: 1st case in 2012 of a teenaged boy in Cebu island in the central Philippines, 4 subsequent cases were foreigners.
http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-09-06/zika-virus-case-confirmed-in-philippines/7817378

[Maps of the Philippines can be accessed at http://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/asia/lgcolor/phcolor.htm and
